### internal/dolt/runner_test.go (pure parts only)

Test `stripANSI()` — the ANSI escape code stripper.

```go
func TestStripANSI_NoEscapes(t *testing.T)
// Input: "plain text"
// Expect: "plain text" (unchanged)

func TestStripANSI_ColorCodes(t *testing.T)
// Input: "\x1b[31mred text\x1b[0m"
// Expect: "red text"

func TestStripANSI_MultipleCodes(t *testing.T)
// Input: "\x1b[1m\x1b[32mbold green\x1b[0m normal"
// Expect: "bold green normal"

func TestStripANSI_EmptyString(t *testing.T)
// Input: ""
// Expect: ""

func TestStripANSI_OnlyEscapes(t *testing.T)
// Input: "\x1b[31m\x1b[0m"
// Expect: ""
```

**Note**: `stripANSI` is currently unexported. Either:
1. Export it as `StripANSI` (preferred — it is genuinely useful externally), OR
2. Test it via `_test.go` in the same package (which has access to unexported funcs)

Option 2 is fine for now since the test file is in `package dolt`.

